This is NOT normal. Anyone under the influence of alcohol, narcotics, or any other sort of drug is incapable of giving consent. If you were drunk, it doesn't matter if you said yes or not, it doesn't count as consensual. But one thing is absolutely certain--this is NOT your fault. You have no reason to feel guilty. It doesn't matter what you said, if you were so drunk that you blacked out anyone who did anything with you took advantage of your condition. Don't listen to anyone try to tell you that you are to blame or anything else because you are a victim here. I would suggest confiding in a close friend or if you feel like you need to speak to someone who can offer professional advice, the counseling center is always available and confidential. But you can overcome this.
